data.meta_description: MARCH FOR BABIES: A MOTHER OF A MOVEMENT - Be part of something big. Join the fight for moms and babies. JOIN US Today.
data.text:
Attention all supporters of healthy babies and strong families in Harrisburg and the surrounding areas.

Walk-A-Thon - April 20, 2024

Join Phi Beta Sigma Fraternity, Inc. and Zeta Phi Beta Sorority, Inc., for the 3rd annual Volunteer-Led, Community Walk to support March for Babies. The event will be held on April 20, 2024, at 10:00 AM, starting at City Island, Harrisburg, PA. This annual event brings together communities across Central, PA to raise funds and awareness for the March of Dimes, the leading nonprofit organization dedicated to improving the health of moms and babies. Registration and activities will start at 9:00a.m.

This year's March for Babies promises to be an unforgettable experience as we walk together in hope of creating a world where every baby is born healthy. Whether you're a seasoned marcher or a first-time participant, your support will make a significant difference in the lives of millions of families.

Together, we can make a difference by funding critical research, advocacy, and educational programs that give every baby a fighting chance. Put on your walking shoes, grab your friends and family, and join us on April 20th for an inspiring day of fun, fitness, and community.

Register here and start fundraising today to help us reach our goal of $15,000 for healthier, stronger babies.

Become a sponsor today!
